## Hints for Future Agents
- Feedback rows are stored post-readback-shaped: created_at as
  isoformat(sep=' ') STRINGS and payload JSON-normalized. Query results and
  the string-window filtering in feedback_stats depend on this.
- The ORM evaluator drops casts on JSON fields (sqlite parity — only CH
  applies clickhouse_cast_json_value) and sorts dynamic fields with an
  existence term first.
- maybe_convert_datetime_operands parity: datetime literals normalize to
  'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS.ffffff' and compare as STRINGS against stored text,
  including sqlite's quirky 'T'-vs-space ordering.
- Default cost seeding parses migrations/006_seed_costs.up.sql (same file
  the sqlite server reads); it runs lazily on first include_costs use.

